Engineering Note for Your Offline Compiler
Since the app must run 100% offline, you won't have a remote server to compile the user's code. To keep things lightweight on a mobile device:

Don't compile raw code: Instead of running a heavy, real-world Java virtual machine inside the phone app, treat the code like string patterns and Abstract Syntax Trees (AST).

How to check answers: Store the correct answers as regex patterns, exact string tokens, or structural trees locally. When the user types or chooses code in the "Drill Station," the app simply compares their input text directly against the local answer key. This makes the app lightning-fast and perfectly functional without using any data or battery-heavy background processing!


